Vice President Biden spoke with former South African President Thabo Mbeki to discuss the situation in Sudan. They discussed the importance of bringing the various Sudanese groups together and establishing a unified approach to ending the conflicts in Sudan. They also emphasized the need for continued pressure on the Sudanese government, opposition leaders, and civil society groups to initiate a national dialogue. The Vice President highlighted the crucial role of African Union leadership in promoting inclusive governance, human rights, and resolving the conflicts in Blue Nile, Southern Kordofan, and Darfur. They agreed to continue coordinating efforts between the African Union and the United States.